      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(daemon): prove Windows schtasks launch without foreground listener [AI]",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix Windows Scheduled Task launch verification so an unrelated foreground gateway listener no longer suppresses the Startup-style fallback after `schtasks /Run`. Tighten launch evidence to require the managed task script process or a process whose argv matches the installed Scheduled Task program arguments, **with a pre-/Run baseline to distinguish pre-existing processes**. Ensure the fallback's port ownership is verified at each call site.\n\n- Baseline process snapshot captured before `/Run`; only processes NOT in the baseline count as launch evidence\n- `launchFallbackTaskScript` returns `boolean` indicating whether the spawned fallback process verified port ownership\n- All three call sites (`restartStartupEntry`, `runScheduledTaskOrThrow`, `activateScheduledTask`) consume the return value — throw or warn on port ownership failure\n\nWhy does this matter now?\n\nWindows users can keep a foreground `openclaw gateway` session open while installing or restarting the managed service; closing that window previously left no gateway because the daemon treated the listener as proof the task had started. After previous attempts (#91198, #91486), the two remaining P2 findings (baseline process evidence, port ownership verification) are now closed.\n\nWhat is intentionally out of scope?\n\n- No change to listener-backed status reporting in `readScheduledTaskRuntime` for status UX\n- No Windows service rewrite or schtasks XML changes\n- No changes outside `src/daemon/schtasks.ts` and its test file\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nCloses #91144\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nRelated #91198 (member PR, closed — P2: unverified-listener filtering gap fixed here by capturing ALL listener PIDs via `readWindowsProcessSnapshot` baseline, not just verified gateway PIDs)\nRelated #91486 (external PR, closed — needed native Windows proof; code direction reused)\nSupersedes #93299 (original version — P2 findings addressed with baseline capture + call site fixes)\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nNo — contributor pool scan pick. ClawSweeper review on the original #93299 identified two P2 findings: baseline process evidence before trusting it (src/daemon/schtasks.ts:1123-1125) and prove fallback port ownership (src/daemon/schtasks.startup-fallback.test.ts:408).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Windows Scheduled Task install/start/restart skipped fallback when a foreground gateway listener was already bound to the configured port; fallback port ownership was unverified\n- **Real environment tested:** Windows 10 (MINGW64_NT-10.0-26200), Node 22.19+, vitest daemon suite with mocked schtasks responses, process snapshot, and verified gateway listener PIDs\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n  ```\n  node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/daemon/schtasks.startup-fallback.test.ts\n  node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/daemon/schtasks.test.ts\n  pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/daemon/schtasks.ts src/daemon/schtasks.startup-fallback.test.ts\n  ```\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n  ```\n   Test Files  2 passed (2)\n        Tests  60 passed (60)\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix:** All 60 tests pass, including the new regression \"verifies port ownership after fallback spawn\" and the three baseline-aware tests (\"does not treat pre-existing process as launch evidence\", \"does not relaunch when gateway Scheduled Task process matches installed arguments\", \"does not relaunch the task script when the scheduled task process is already starting\")\n- **What was not tested:** Live native Windows Task Scheduler handoff (foreground gateway → install → close → status --deep --require-rpc) was not run because the local Windows CLI build has a DLL init failure unrelated to the daemon code change. The source-level regression coverage uses the repository's existing Windows schtasks mocks and covers the full decision surface.\n- **Proof limitations:** L2+ proof via vitest with real schtasks module functions and mocked OS calls; L3 deferred to environment with functioning Windows CLI build\n- **Before evidence:** Original issue #91144 — foreground gateway works, `openclaw gateway install` accepts, closing the foreground window yields `ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:18789`. Previous PRs #91198 and #91486 were blocked by the same P2 gaps now addressed here.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nWhich commands did you run?\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/daemon/schtasks.startup-fallback.test.ts src/daemon/schtasks.test.ts` — 60/60 passed\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/daemon/schtasks.ts src/daemon/schtasks.startup-fallback.test.ts` — clean\n\nWhat regression coverage was added or updated?\n\n- `does not treat a foreground gateway listener as gateway Scheduled Task launch evidence`\n- `does not treat pre-existing process as launch evidence when process existed in baseline`\n- `does not relaunch when the gateway Scheduled Task process matches installed arguments`\n- `verifies port ownership after fallback spawn`\n- `does not relaunch when the node Scheduled Task process is already running` (updated with baseline-aware mock)\n- `does not relaunch the task script when the scheduled task process is already starting` (updated with baseline-aware mock)\n- `restartStartupEntry` now warns on port ownership failure\n- `runScheduledTaskOrThrow` now throws on port ownership failure\n- `activateScheduledTask` now warns on port ownership failure\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known?\n\nWith `findVerifiedGatewayListenerPidsOnPortSync` returning a foreground PID and schtasks stuck at `not-yet-run`, install did not call the fallback spawn path. The three \"does not relaunch\" tests also failed because the baseline comparison was missing.\n\nIf no test was added, why not?\n\nN/A — regression tests added or updated.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes`)\n\nYes. Windows gateway install/start/restart now warns or throws when the fallback process spawned but cannot verify port ownership, instead of silently succeeding. The restart path prints a warning; the install path throws an error.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`No`)\n\nNo.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`No`)\n\nNo.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\nWindows gateway install/start/restart may now throw an error if the fallback gateway process does not appear as a verified listener on the configured port within 2 seconds. In environments where the gateway is slow to start (e.g., high-load machines or cold starts), this could cause a false negative.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\nThe 2-second wait and port ownership check only run when `childPid` is available. On the install path, the error is thrown (matching the function name `runScheduledTaskOrThrow`). On the restart and startup-entry paths, a warning is written to stdout but the operation still completes. Existing behavior for the common case (fallback starts successfully or no PID tracking) is unchanged.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\n- Maintainer / ClawSweeper review\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\n- CI checks (requires Crabbox/Testbox for broad CI — local vitest + format pass)\n- ClawSweeper re-review for updated verdict\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\nPrevious ClawSweeper review on #93299 (Commit e1055a6d7fb3):\n- [P2] Baseline process evidence before trusting it — addressed: `readWindowsProcessSnapshot()` baseline captured before `/Run`, all `hasLaunchEvidence` process checks compare against baseline\n- [P2] Prove the fallback owns the port — addressed: `launchFallbackTaskScript` returns `boolean`, all three call sites consume the return value (throw or warn)\n- [P1] Native Windows proof — partially addressed: Windows test environment confirmed, L2+ vitest proof provided, L3 blocked by unrelated CLI DLL issue on local Windows build\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-91144-schtasks-listener-proof",
